
## Evan Arapostathis

Evan Anthony Arapostathis (born October 30, 1963) is a former American football player for the St. Louis Cardinals in the National Football League (NFL). The punter played one season for the Cardinals in 1986. In 1987, he joined the Denver Broncos during the NFL Players strike. He was kept on the Inactive Players roster for the 1987 season. He ran the ABCD Kicking Camps with former NFL greats, Darren Bennett, John Carney and Brad Daluiso having coached all of them. Evan graduated from Eastern Illinois and high school at Helix High School.

